as.list method for the "GeneralData" class

as.list-GeneralData-method.Rd

as.list method for the "GeneralData" class

# S4 method for GeneralData
as.list(x, ...)

Arguments

x

the GeneralData object we want to convert
…

unused

Value

a list of all slots in x

Examples


# Create some data of class 'Data'
myData <- Data(x=c(0.1,0.5,1.5,3,6,10,10,10),
               y=c(0,0,0,0,0,0,1,0),
               doseGrid=c(0.1,0.5,1.5,3,6,
               seq(from=10,to=80,by=2)))
#> Warning: Used default patient IDs!
#> Warning: Used best guess cohort indices!

# Converting Data object to list
as.list(myData)
#> $x
#> [1]  0.1  0.5  1.5  3.0  6.0 10.0 10.0 10.0
#> 
#> $y
#> [1] 0 0 0 0 0 0 1 0
#> 
#> $doseGrid
#>  [1]  0.1  0.5  1.5  3.0  6.0 10.0 12.0 14.0 16.0 18.0 20.0 22.0 24.0 26.0 28.0
#> [16] 30.0 32.0 34.0 36.0 38.0 40.0 42.0 44.0 46.0 48.0 50.0 52.0 54.0 56.0 58.0
#> [31] 60.0 62.0 64.0 66.0 68.0 70.0 72.0 74.0 76.0 78.0 80.0
#> 
#> $nGrid
#> [1] 41
#> 
#> $xLevel
#> [1] 1 2 3 4 5 6 6 6
#> 
#> $placebo
#> [1] FALSE
#> 
#> $ID
#> [1] 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8
#> 
#> $cohort
#> [1] 1 2 3 4 5 6 6 6
#> 
#> $nObs
#> [1] 8
#>
